69int X509at_get_attr_count(const STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *x)
70{
71 return sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_num(x);
72}
73
74int X509at_get_attr_by_NID(const STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *x, int nid,
75 int lastpos)
76{
77 const ASN1_OBJECT *obj;
78
79 obj = OBJ_nid2obj(nid);
80 if (obj == NULL)
81 return (-2);
82 return (X509at_get_attr_by_OBJ(x, obj, lastpos));
83}
84
85int X509at_get_attr_by_OBJ(const STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *sk,
86 const ASN1_OBJECT *obj, int lastpos)
87{
88 int n;
89 X509_ATTRIBUTE *ex;
90
91 if (sk == NULL)
92 return (-1);
93 lastpos++;
94 if (lastpos < 0)
95 lastpos = 0;
96 n = sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_num(sk);
97 for (; lastpos < n; lastpos++) {
98 ex = sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_value(sk, lastpos);
99 if (OBJ_cmp(ex->object, obj) == 0)
100 return (lastpos);
101 }
102 return (-1);
103}
104
105X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509at_get_attr(const STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *x, int loc)
106{
107 if (x == NULL || loc < 0 || sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_num(x) <= (size_t)loc)
108 return NULL;
109 else
110 return sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_value(x, loc);
111}
112
113X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509at_delete_attr(STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *x, int loc)
114{
115 X509_ATTRIBUTE *ret;
116
117 if (x == NULL || loc < 0 || sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_num(x) <= (size_t)loc)
118 return (NULL);
119 ret = sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_delete(x, loc);
120 return (ret);
121}
122
123STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *X509at_add1_attr(STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) **x,
124 X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr)
125{
126 X509_ATTRIBUTE *new_attr = NULL;
127 STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *sk = NULL;
128
129 if (x == NULL) {
130 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
131 goto err2;
132 }
133
134 if (*x == NULL) {
135 if ((sk = sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_new_null()) == NULL)
136 goto err;
137 } else
138 sk = *x;
139
140 if ((new_attr = X509_ATTRIBUTE_dup(attr)) == NULL)
141 goto err2;
142 if (!sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_push(sk, new_attr))
143 goto err;
144 if (*x == NULL)
145 *x = sk;
146 return (sk);
147 err:
148 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
149 err2:
150 if (new_attr != NULL)
151 X509_ATTRIBUTE_free(new_attr);
152 if (sk != NULL)
153 sk_X509_ATTRIBUTE_free(sk);
154 return (NULL);
155}
156
157STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *X509at_add1_attr_by_OBJ(STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE)
158 **x, const ASN1_OBJECT *obj,
159 int type,
160 const unsigned char *bytes,
161 int len)
162{
163 X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr;
164 STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *ret;
165 attr = X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_OBJ(NULL, obj, type, bytes, len);
166 if (!attr)
167 return 0;
168 ret = X509at_add1_attr(x, attr);
169 X509_ATTRIBUTE_free(attr);
170 return ret;
171}

204void *X509at_get0_data_by_OBJ(STACK_OF(X509_ATTRIBUTE) *x,
205 ASN1_OBJECT *obj, int lastpos, int type)
206{
207 int i;
208 X509_ATTRIBUTE *at;
209 i = X509at_get_attr_by_OBJ(x, obj, lastpos);
210 if (i == -1)
211 return NULL;
212 if ((lastpos <= -2) && (X509at_get_attr_by_OBJ(x, obj, i) != -1))
213 return NULL;
214 at = X509at_get_attr(x, i);
215 if (lastpos <= -3 && (X509_ATTRIBUTE_count(at) != 1))
216 return NULL;
217 return X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_data(at, 0, type, NULL);
218}
219
220X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_NID(X509_ATTRIBUTE **attr, int nid,
221 int attrtype, const void *data,
222 int len)
223{
224 const ASN1_OBJECT *obj;
225
226 obj = OBJ_nid2obj(nid);
227 if (obj == NULL) {
228 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_UNKNOWN_NID);
229 return (NULL);
230 }
231 return X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_OBJ(attr, obj, attrtype, data, len);
232}
233
234X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_OBJ(X509_ATTRIBUTE **attr,
235 const ASN1_OBJECT *obj,
236 int attrtype, const void *data,
237 int len)
238{
239 X509_ATTRIBUTE *ret;
240
241 if ((attr == NULL) || (*attr == NULL)) {
242 if ((ret = X509_ATTRIBUTE_new()) == NULL) {
243 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
244 return (NULL);
245 }
246 } else
247 ret = *attr;
248
249 if (!X509_ATTRIBUTE_set1_object(ret, obj))
250 goto err;
251 if (!X509_ATTRIBUTE_set1_data(ret, attrtype, data, len))
252 goto err;
253
254 if ((attr != NULL) && (*attr == NULL))
255 *attr = ret;
256 return (ret);
257 err:
258 if ((attr == NULL) || (ret != *attr))
259 X509_ATTRIBUTE_free(ret);
260 return (NULL);
261}
262
263X509_ATTRIBUTE *X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_txt(X509_ATTRIBUTE **attr,
264 const char *attrname, int type,
265 const unsigned char *bytes,
266 int len)
267{
268 ASN1_OBJECT *obj;
269 X509_ATTRIBUTE *nattr;
270
271 obj = OBJ_txt2obj(attrname, 0);
272 if (obj == NULL) {
273 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_INVALID_FIELD_NAME);
274 ERR_add_error_data(2, "name=", attrname);
275 return (NULL);
276 }
277 nattr = X509_ATTRIBUTE_create_by_OBJ(attr, obj, type, bytes, len);
278 ASN1_OBJECT_free(obj);
279 return nattr;
280}
281
282int X509_ATTRIBUTE_set1_object(X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr, const ASN1_OBJECT *obj)
283{
284 if ((attr == NULL) || (obj == NULL))
285 return (0);
286 ASN1_OBJECT_free(attr->object);
287 attr->object = OBJ_dup(obj);
288 return attr->object != NULL;
289}
290
291int X509_ATTRIBUTE_set1_data(X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr, int attrtype,
292 const void *data, int len)
293{
294 ASN1_TYPE *ttmp = NULL;
295 ASN1_STRING *stmp = NULL;
296 int atype = 0;
297 if (!attr)
298 return 0;
299 if (attrtype & MBSTRING_FLAG) {
300 stmp = ASN1_STRING_set_by_NID(NULL, data, len, attrtype,
301 OBJ_obj2nid(attr->object));
302 if (!stmp) {
303 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_ASN1_LIB);
304 return 0;
305 }
306 atype = stmp->type;
307 } else if (len != -1) {
308 if (!(stmp = ASN1_STRING_type_new(attrtype)))
309 goto err;
310 if (!ASN1_STRING_set(stmp, data, len))
311 goto err;
312 atype = attrtype;
313 }
314 /*
315 * This is a bit naughty because the attribute should really have at
316 * least one value but some types use and zero length SET and require
317 * this.
318 */
319 if (attrtype == 0) {
320 ASN1_STRING_free(stmp);
321 return 1;
322 }
323 if (!(ttmp = ASN1_TYPE_new()))
324 goto err;
325 if ((len == -1) && !(attrtype & MBSTRING_FLAG)) {
326 if (!ASN1_TYPE_set1(ttmp, attrtype, data))
327 goto err;
328 } else {
329 ASN1_TYPE_set(ttmp, atype, stmp);
330 stmp = NULL;
331 }
332 if (!sk_ASN1_TYPE_push(attr->set, ttmp))
333 goto err;
334 return 1;
335 err:
336 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
337 ASN1_TYPE_free(ttmp);
338 ASN1_STRING_free(stmp);
339 return 0;
340}
341
342int X509_ATTRIBUTE_count(const X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr)
343{
344 return sk_ASN1_TYPE_num(attr->set);
345}
346
347ASN1_OBJECT *X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_object(X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr)
348{
349 if (attr == NULL)
350 return (NULL);
351 return (attr->object);
352}
353
354void *X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_data(X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr, int idx,
355 int attrtype, void *unused)
356{
357 ASN1_TYPE *ttmp;
358 ttmp = X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_type(attr, idx);
359 if (!ttmp)
360 return NULL;
361 if (attrtype != ASN1_TYPE_get(ttmp)) {
362 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, X509_R_WRONG_TYPE);
363 return NULL;
364 }
365 return (void *)asn1_type_value_as_pointer(ttmp);
366}
367
368ASN1_TYPE *X509_ATTRIBUTE_get0_type(X509_ATTRIBUTE *attr, int idx)
369{
370 if (attr == NULL)
371 return NULL;
372 if (idx >= X509_ATTRIBUTE_count(attr))
373 return NULL;
374 return sk_ASN1_TYPE_value(attr->set, idx);
375}
